OL,3,CWoman jailed for life for 'brutal'
OL,4,Cmurder of Caroline Glachan in 1996
OL,6,FJudge Lord Braid said Brand had been
OL,7,Fconvicted of a "brutal" murder.
OL,9,FHe said that while Brand did not take
OL,10,Fpart in the assault itself, she shared
OL,11,Fin responsibility for the crime
OL,12,Fbecause she left Caroline face down in
OL,13,Fthe river while she was still alive
OL,14,Fand was part of a plan of "murderous
OL,15,Fviolence".
OL,17,FHe said: "Caroline was a popular
OL,18,Fteenager. She was a lover of life. Due
OL,19,Fin part to you she has been deprived
OL,20,Fof living that life".
